# Math Point Type Rule

- When editing math-related code, include `packages/math/src/types.ts` in context.
- Use the canonical `Point` type instead of ad-hoc `{ x, y }` object types.
- Keep math utility signatures consistent with existing exported types.

## How to verify

- Confirm math changes reference existing types from `packages/math/src/types.ts`.
- Confirm new function signatures use `Point` where coordinates are represented.
- Confirm no new inline `{ x, y }` type literals are introduced in math APIs.
- Confirm exports remain type-compatible with package consumers.
